- "Recent sales" refers to the most recent sale for each customer;
- "Top 10" is determined by the highest total revenue from sales;
- "Vehicle models" are identified by their make and year.

- "blossomed with more than one sale" refers to categories that have sold more than one vehicle;
- "total earnings" refers to the sum of sale prices for each category;
- "average price" refers to the average sale price for each category;
- "blossoms (vehicles)" refers to the total number of vehicles sold in each category.

- "Average price" is calculated by summing all prices in a category and dividing by the number of vehicles in that category;
- "Soars above the $20,000 mark" means the average price is greater than $20,000;
- "Listed from the most expensive to the least" refers to the order of results from highest to lowest average price.

- "Total sales" refers to the number of vehicles sold for each make;
- "Popular make" is determined by the highest total sales;
- "Associated categories" are the categories to which the vehicles of each make belong.

- "Multiple test drives" implies the vehicle has been driven by more than one potential buyer;
- "Specific features" refer to features such as a sunroof or leather interior;
- The query focuses on vehicles that have been sold, indicating a completed transaction.

- "taken a vehicle for a spin" refers to test-driving a vehicle;
- "brought one home" refers to purchasing a vehicle;
- "in the same category" means the category of the test-driven vehicle matches the category of the purchased vehicle.

- "rake in more than double the average income of their peers" refers to total sales revenue being greater than twice the average sale price across all sales;
- "brands" refers to the make of the vehicle;
- "total treasure" refers to the total sales revenue.

- The "highest sale price" refers to the maximum sale price for each make;
- "More than one sale" means the make has at least two sales;
- "Descending order of the number of sales" means the makes with the most sales appear first.
